4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REQUIRING MOTOR VEHICLE INSURANCE POLICIES TO
5 COVER COSTS FOR RECOVERY AND SERVICES FOR COMMERCIAL TOW TRUCK OPERATORS;
6 AMENDING SECTION 61-6-103, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN APPLICABILITY DATE.”
7
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
9
10 Section 1. Section 61-6-103, MCA, is amended to read:
11 "61-6-103. Motor vehicle liability policy minimum limits -- other requirements. (1) A motor
12 vehicle liability policy must:
13 (a) designate by explicit description or by appropriate reference all motor vehicles with respect to
14 the coverage to be granted; and
15 (b) insure the person named in the policy and any other person, as insured, using any motor
16 vehicle or motor vehicles with the express or implied permission of the named insured, against loss from the
17 liability imposed by law for damages, including costs for recovery and debris cleanup services, such as liquids
18 and other material at the scene of an accident, by a commercial tow truck operator as defined in 61-8-903,
19 arising out of the ownership, maintenance, or use of the motor vehicle or motor vehicles within the United
20 States of America or Canada, subject to limits exclusive of interest and costs, with respect to each motor
21 vehicle, as follows:
22 (i) $25,000 because of bodily injury to or death of one person in any one accident and subject to
23 the limit for one person;
24 (ii) $50,000 because of bodily injury to or death of two or more persons in any one accident; and
25 (iii) $20,000 because of injury to or destruction of property of others in any one accident.
26 (2) An operator's policy of liability insurance must insure the person named as insured in the policy
27 against loss from the liability imposed upon the operator by law for damages arising out of the use by the
28 operator of any motor vehicle not owned by the operator, within the same territorial limits and subject to the
