1 same limits of liability that are set forth in subsection (1) with respect to the operator's policy of liability
2 insurance.
3 (3) A motor vehicle liability policy must state the name and address of the named insured, the
4 coverage afforded by the policy, the premium charged for the policy, the policy period, and the limits of liability
5 and contain an agreement or be endorsed that insurance is provided under the policy in accordance with the
6 coverage defined in this part with respect to bodily injury and death or property damage, or both, and is subject
7 to all the provisions of this part.
8 (4) A motor vehicle liability policy need not insure any liability under any workers' compensation
9 law or any liability on account of bodily injury to or death of an employee of the insured while engaged in the
10 employment, other than domestic, of the insured or while engaged in the operation, maintenance, or repair of a
11 motor vehicle or any liability for damage to property owned by, rented to, in charge of, or transported by the
12 insured.
13 (5) A motor vehicle liability policy is subject to the following provisions, which need not be
14 contained in the policy:
15 (a) The liability of the insurance carrier with respect to the insurance required by this part becomes
16 absolute whenever injury or damage covered by the motor vehicle liability policy occurs. The policy may not be
17 canceled or annulled as to the liability by any agreement between the insurance carrier and the insured after
18 the occurrence of the injury or damage. A statement made by the insured or on behalf of the insured and a
19 violation of the policy may not defeat or void the policy.
20 (b) The satisfaction by the insured of a judgment for the injury or damage may not be a condition
21 precedent to the right or duty of the insurance carrier to make payment on account of the injury or damage.
22 (c) The insurance carrier has the right to settle any claim covered by the policy, and if the
23 settlement is made in good faith, the amount is deductible from the limits of liability specified in subsection
24 (1)(b).
25 (d) The policy, the written application for the policy, if any, and any rider or endorsement that does
26 not conflict with the provisions of this part constitute the entire contract between the parties.
27 (6) A motor vehicle policy is not subject to cancellation, termination, nonrenewal, or premium
28 increase due to injury or damage incurred by the insured or operator unless the insured or operator is found to
