10 (8) A motor vehicle liability policy may provide that the insured shall reimburse the insurance
11 carrier for any payment the insurance carrier would not have been obligated to make under the terms of the
12 policy except for the provisions of this part.
13 (9) A motor vehicle liability policy may provide for the prorating of the insurance under the policy
14 with other valid and collectible insurance.
15 (10) The requirements for a motor vehicle liability policy may be fulfilled by the policies of one or
16 more insurance carriers, which policies together meet the requirements.
17 (11) Any binder issued pending the issuance of a motor vehicle liability policy fulfills the
18 requirements for the policy.
19 (12) A reduced limits endorsement may not be issued by a company to be attached to a policy
20 issued in compliance with this section."
